race.comment: ROTAGILLA (9) has come along in leaps and bounds this time in and adept in all conditions. Faces his stiffest test to date after powering late with the 59kg when a narrow winner over 1800m at Rosehill. Should appreciate the good tempo with the weight drop. Hard to hold out. COLLECT YOUR CASH (1) got his desired conditions first-up when a tenacious winner over the mile at Kembla Grange in the heavy (8) going. Clearly come back well and can get the job done again. SOSINO (14) racing without luck with the big weights and ticks a few boxes today on the limit. Senior rider goes aboard and will give a ton of cheek at the good odds. SUN GOD (4) just under a month between runs for this after defeating a good field over 1850m at Newcastle. Kept ticking over with a 1100m trial at Canterbury. Stays in the mix. POCKETING (2) meets SUN GOD better at the weights for his narrow second and will appreciate the sting out of the track. Gets Nock's claim and has the speed to get across from the wide draw.
